shells

line,

slope;

can-

nister

bayonets

to

white
comrades

black
men

wild
cheer

living
hundreds

works

cyclone;
they

seized
the
cannon
and

the
fleeing
foe,

who,
in

toward
Petersburg,
to

their
main
line
of
intrenchments

east.

the

work
of
the
5th
and
22nd
Phalanx

com¬

pleted

road
made
clear

the
18th

Martin-

dale,

river

to

open

Never¬

theless,

a

line
of

the

division
numbered

about
3,000,

portion

ing,

was
a
march
that
veterans
might
falter
in,

or

The
steady
black
line
advanced

a
few
rods

guns

a
lull,—they

march,

a
most
galling,

artillery

one

o'clock,—four

hours,—exposed

less
